cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with skin lesion analysis using deep neural networks. The use of multi-task learning also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques for image analysis. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) could also be a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the segmentation and classification of skin lesions. Finally, Multimedia (cs.MM) could be another possible sub-category as the paper involves the analysis of dermoscopic images.
